=== ERROR BOUNDARIES ANALYSIS ===

error.tsx files: 75
not-found.tsx files: 1 (root only)

Coverage:
- Root app/error.tsx exists — catches unhandled errors globally — GOOD
- 75 route groups have error.tsx — GOOD coverage for major sections
- ~190 route groups MISSING error.tsx — these fall through to root error boundary

Key protected areas:
- app/admin/error.tsx — EXISTS
- app/lms/error.tsx — EXISTS
- app/instructor/error.tsx — EXISTS
- app/staff-portal/error.tsx — EXISTS
- app/workforce-board/error.tsx — EXISTS
- app/student-portal/error.tsx — EXISTS
- app/store/error.tsx — EXISTS
- app/login/error.tsx — EXISTS

Missing error.tsx in notable areas:
- app/(auth)/ — auth flow errors fall to root
- app/studio/ — dev studio errors fall to root
- app/ai-studio/ — AI studio errors fall to root
- app/compliance/ — compliance pages fall to root

ASSESSMENT: MEDIUM — Root error boundary catches everything, but ~190 route groups
lack specific error handling. For gov quality, each major section should have its own
error boundary with appropriate messaging.

Error message exposure:
- Previous audit noted 394 routes expose error.message to clients
- This leaks internal error details (stack traces, DB errors) to end users
- Gov scanners flag this as information disclosure vulnerability
